==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Myeloidin
<hw>My`e*loid"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Myelin</ets> + <ets>-oid</ets> + <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance, present in the protoplasm
of the retinal epithelium cells, and resembling, if not identical with,
the substance (<xex>myelin</xex>) forming the medullary sheaths of nerve
fibers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myelon</ent>⟦br⟧
